Common transport (MHD) Prague will introduce the pus in their ticket system on Wednesday
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, it will be recorded in the history of Pražský Doprarní podnik (the Prague Transport Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will get into the subway, trams and buses, which, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, the latter is accessible to almost one hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard puzzle card.
Passengers can buy a coupon for 30 days or 90 days (it will be valid from 1 January 2009) and both to record it on their card in the information points and offices of the Doprarnní podnik (the Transport Agency), located in the metro stations Muzeum, Můstek, Nadrazi Holeshovice, Andel, Rostyly, Letňany, Kobilisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy online coupons on the Doprahrní vodnik websites: www.dpp.cz.
Over four hundred people benefited from the service in the morning.
Those who will start using the online store can permanently forget the tickets in the metro stations, where they had to so far become impatient in long queues in order to obtain tickets in paper.
In fact, they will buy their coupon online and will be registered on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knikhna (municipal libraries).
"In these contact points, there is the availability of passengers with trained staff, which will help those interested in online purchases and will also record the coupon they bought on their card," said the spokesperson of the Martin Opatrny project.
In addition to libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic drops on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, recalling the machines to compose the tickets and passengers have perhaps already noticed them in the metro stations Roztyly, Budjejovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be twenty-four," Opatrny added.
A machine will control the coupon instead of the driver
